{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Someone once said that politics is, of course, \"showbiz for ugly people.\""},{"time":6000,"text":"So, on that basis, I feel like I've really arrived."},{"time":10000,"text":"The other thing to think of is what an honor it is, as a politician,"},{"time":13000,"text":"to give a TED talk, particularly here in the U.K.,"},{"time":16000,"text":"where the reputation of politics, with the expenses scandal, has sunk so low."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"There was even a story recently that scientists had thought about"},{"time":26000,"text":"actually replacing rats in their experiments with politicians."},{"time":31000,"text":"And someone asked,\"Why?\""},{"time":33000,"text":"and they said, \"Well, there's no shortage of politicians,"},{"time":37000,"text":"no one really minds what happens to them"},{"time":40000,"text":"and, after all, there are some things that rats just won't do.\""},{"time":43000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"Now, I know you all love data, so I'm starting with a data-rich slide."},{"time":49000,"text":"This, I think, is the most important fact to bear in mind"},{"time":52000,"text":"in British politics or American politics,"},{"time":56000,"text":"and that is: We have run out of money."},{"time":58000,"text":"We have vast budget deficits."},{"time":61000,"text":"This is my global public debt clock,"},{"time":64000,"text":"and, as you can see, it's 32 trillion and counting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"And I think what this leads to"},{"time":70000,"text":"is a very simple recognition,"},{"time":73000,"text":"that there's one question in politics at the moment above all other,"},{"time":76000,"text":"and it's this one: How do we make things better without spending more money?"},{"time":81000,"text":"Because there isn't going to be a lot of money to improve public services,"},{"time":85000,"text":"or to improve government, or to improve so many of the things"},{"time":88000,"text":"that politicians talk about."},{"time":90000,"text":"So what follows from that is that if you think it's all about money --"},{"time":96000,"text":"you can only measure success in public services"},{"time":99000,"text":"in health care and education and policing by spending more money,"},{"time":103000,"text":"you can only measure progress by spending money --"},{"time":106000,"text":"you're going to have a pretty miserable time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"But if you think a whole lot of other things matter that lead up to well being --"},{"time":113000,"text":"things like your family relationships, friendship, community, values --"},{"time":116000,"text":"then, actually, this is an incredibly exciting time to be in politics."},{"time":121000,"text":"And the really simple argument I want to make tonight,"},{"time":123000,"text":"the really straightforward argument is this:"},{"time":125000,"text":"That if we combine the right political philosophy, the right political thinking,"},{"time":131000,"text":"with the incredible information revolution that has taken place,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and that all of you know so much more about than I do,"},{"time":139000,"text":"I think there's an incredible opportunity to actually remake politics,"},{"time":143000,"text":"remake government, remake public services,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and achieve what's up on that slide, which is a big increase in our well-being."},{"time":151000,"text":"That's the argument I want to make tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"So, starting with the political philosophy."},{"time":157000,"text":"Now I'm not saying for a minute that British Conservatives have all the answers."},{"time":160000,"text":"Of course we don't."},{"time":162000,"text":"But there are two things at heart that I think drive a conservative philosophy"},{"time":167000,"text":"that are really relevant to this whole debate."},{"time":169000,"text":"The first is this: We believe that if you give people"},{"time":171000,"text":"more power and control over their lives,"},{"time":174000,"text":"if you give people more choice,"},{"time":176000,"text":"if you put them in the driving seat,"},{"time":178000,"text":"then actually, you can create a stronger and better society."},{"time":181000,"text":"And if you marry this fact with the incredible abundance"},{"time":185000,"text":"of information that we have in our world today,"},{"time":187000,"text":"I think you can completely, as I've said,"},{"time":189000,"text":"remake politics, remake government, remake your public services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"The second thing we believe is we believe in going with the grain of human nature."},{"time":198000,"text":"Politics and politicians will only succeed"},{"time":201000,"text":"if they actually try and treat with people as they are,"},{"time":206000,"text":"rather than as they would like them to be."},{"time":209000,"text":"Now, if you combine this very simple, very conservative thought --"},{"time":212000,"text":"go with the grain of human nature --"},{"time":214000,"text":"with all the advances in behavioral economics,"},{"time":217000,"text":"some of which we were just hearing about,"},{"time":219000,"text":"again, I think we can achieve a real increase in well-being,"},{"time":222000,"text":"in happiness, in a stronger society"},{"time":225000,"text":"without necessarily having to spend a whole lot more money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"Now, why do I think now is the moment to make this argument?"},{"time":233000,"text":"Well, I'm afraid you're going to suffer a short, condensed history lesson"},{"time":237000,"text":"about what I would say are the three passages of history:"},{"time":240000,"text":"the pre-bureaucratic age, the bureaucratic age"},{"time":244000,"text":"and what we now live in, which I think is a post-bureaucratic age."},{"time":247000,"text":"A simpler way of thinking of it"},{"time":249000,"text":"is that we have gone from a world of local control,"},{"time":253000,"text":"then we went to a world of central control,"},{"time":256000,"text":"and now we're in a world of people control."},{"time":258000,"text":"Local power, central power, now, people power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"Now, here is King Cnut, king a thousand years ago."},{"time":265000,"text":"Thought he could turn back the waves; couldn't turn back the waves."},{"time":268000,"text":"Couldn't actually turn back very much,"},{"time":270000,"text":"because if you were king a thousand years ago,"},{"time":272000,"text":"while it still took hours and hours and weeks and weeks to traverse your own country,"},{"time":277000,"text":"there wasn't much you were in charge of."},{"time":279000,"text":"You weren't in charge of policing, justice, education, health, welfare."},{"time":282000,"text":"You could just about go to war and that was about it."},{"time":286000,"text":"This was the pre-bureaucratic age,"},{"time":288000,"text":"an age in which everything had to be local."},{"time":292000,"text":"You had to have local control because there was no nationally-available information"},{"time":297000,"text":"because travel was so restricted."},{"time":299000,"text":"So this was the pre-bureaucratic age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"Next part of the cold history lesson,"},{"time":303000,"text":"the lovely picture of the British Industrial Revolution."},{"time":306000,"text":"Suddenly, all sorts of transport, travel information were possible,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and this gave birth to, what I like to call, the bureaucratic age."},{"time":314000,"text":"And hopefully this slide is going to morph beautifully. There we are."},{"time":317000,"text":"Suddenly, you have the big, strong, central state."},{"time":321000,"text":"It was able -- but only it was able -- to organize"},{"time":325000,"text":"health care, education, policing, justice."},{"time":328000,"text":"And it was a world of, as I say, not local power, but now central power."},{"time":333000,"text":"It had sucked all that power up from the localities."},{"time":336000,"text":"It was able to do that itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"The next great stage, which all of you are so familiar with:"},{"time":342000,"text":"the massive information revolution."},{"time":345000,"text":"Just consider this one fact:"},{"time":348000,"text":"One hundred years ago, sending these 10 words cost 50 dollars."},{"time":352000,"text":"Right now, here we are linked up to Long Beach and everywhere else,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and all these secret locations for a fraction of that cost,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and we can send and receive huge quantities of information"},{"time":362000,"text":"without it costing anything."},{"time":364000,"text":"So we're now living in a post-bureaucratic age,"},{"time":369000,"text":"where genuine people power is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Now, what does this mean for our politics,"},{"time":376000,"text":"for our public services, for our government?"},{"time":379000,"text":"Well I can't, in the time I've got, give huge numbers of examples,"},{"time":383000,"text":"but let me just give a few of the ways that life can change."},{"time":388000,"text":"And this is so obvious, in a way, because"},{"time":390000,"text":"you think about how all of you have changed"},{"time":392000,"text":"the way we shop, the way we travel, the way that business is done."},{"time":396000,"text":"That is already happened; the information and Internet revolution"},{"time":399000,"text":"has actually gone all the way through our societies in so many different ways,"},{"time":403000,"text":"but it hasn't, in every way, yet touched our government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"So, how could this happen?"},{"time":408000,"text":"Well, I think there are three chief ways that it should make an enormous difference:"},{"time":412000,"text":"in transparency, in greater choice and in accountability,"},{"time":416000,"text":"in giving us that genuine people power."},{"time":420000,"text":"If we take transparency, here is one of my favorite websites,"},{"time":424000,"text":"the Missouri Accountability Portal."},{"time":427000,"text":"In the old days, only the government could hold the information,"},{"time":430000,"text":"and only a few elected people could try and grab that information"},{"time":434000,"text":"and question it and challenge it."},{"time":436000,"text":"Now here, on one website, one state in America,"},{"time":440000,"text":"every single dollar spent by that government"},{"time":444000,"text":"is searchable, is analyzable, is checkable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"Think of the huge change that means:"},{"time":449000,"text":"Any business that wants to bid for a government contract"},{"time":452000,"text":"can see what currently is being spent."},{"time":454000,"text":"Anyone thinking, \"I could do that service better, I could deliver it cheaper,\""},{"time":457000,"text":"it's all available there."},{"time":459000,"text":"We have only, in government and in politics,"},{"time":462000,"text":"started to scratch the surface of what people are doing in the commercial world"},{"time":466000,"text":"with the information revolution."},{"time":468000,"text":"So, complete transparency will make a huge difference."},{"time":471000,"text":"In this country, if we win the election,"},{"time":473000,"text":"we are going to make all government spending over 25,000 pounds"},{"time":477000,"text":"transparent and available online, searchable for anyone to see."},{"time":481000,"text":"We're going to make every contract -- we're announcing this today --"},{"time":485000,"text":"available on the Internet so anyone can see"},{"time":487000,"text":"what the terms are, what the conditions are,"},{"time":489000,"text":"driving huge value for money,"},{"time":491000,"text":"but also huge increases, I believe, in well-being as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497000,"text":"Choice. Now you all shop online, compare online, do everything online,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and yet this revolution has hardly touched the surface"},{"time":505000,"text":"of public services like education, or health care or policing,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and you're going to see this change massively."},{"time":512000,"text":"We should be making this change"},{"time":514000,"text":"with the information revolution in our country,"},{"time":516000,"text":"with searchable health sites, so you can see what operations work out properly,"},{"time":521000,"text":"what records doctors have, the cleanliness of hospitals,"},{"time":524000,"text":"who does best at infection control --"},{"time":526000,"text":"all of the information that would once be locked in the Department of Health"},{"time":530000,"text":"is now available for all of us to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"And the third of these big changes: accountability."},{"time":537000,"text":"This, I think, is a huge change."},{"time":539000,"text":"It is a crime map. This is a crime map from Chicago."},{"time":543000,"text":"So, instead of having a situation where only the police have the information"},{"time":546000,"text":"about which crimes are committed where,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and we have to employ people in government"},{"time":552000,"text":"to try and hold the police to account,"},{"time":554000,"text":"suddenly, we've got this vast opportunity for people power,"},{"time":557000,"text":"where we, as citizens, can see what crimes are being committed --"},{"time":560000,"text":"where, when and by whom --"},{"time":562000,"text":"and we can hold the police to account."},{"time":564000,"text":"And you can see this looks a bit like a chef's hat,"},{"time":566000,"text":"but actually that's an assault, the one in blue."},{"time":569000,"text":"You can see what crime is committed where,"},{"time":571000,"text":"and you have the opportunity to hold your police force to account."},{"time":574000,"text":"So those three ways -- transparency, accountability and choice --"},{"time":580000,"text":"will make a huge difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"Now I also said the other principle"},{"time":584000,"text":"that I think we should work on is understanding of people,"},{"time":586000,"text":"is recognizing that going with the grain of human nature"},{"time":590000,"text":"you can achieve so much more."},{"time":592000,"text":"Now, we're got a huge revolution in understanding"},{"time":594000,"text":"of why people behave in the way that they do,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and a great opportunity to put that knowledge and information to greater use."},{"time":602000,"text":"We're working with some of these people."},{"time":604000,"text":"We're being advised by some of these people, as was said,"},{"time":607000,"text":"to try and bring all the experience to book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Let me just give you one example that I think is incredibly simple, and I love."},{"time":615000,"text":"We want to get people to be more energy efficient."},{"time":617000,"text":"Why? It cuts fuel poverty, it cuts their bills,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and it cuts carbon emissions at the same time."},{"time":623000,"text":"How do you do it?"},{"time":625000,"text":"Well, we've had government information campaigns over the years"},{"time":627000,"text":"when they tell you to switch off the lights when you leave the home."},{"time":630000,"text":"We even had -- one government minister once told us to"},{"time":633000,"text":"brush our teeth in the dark."},{"time":635000,"text":"I don't think they lasted very long."},{"time":637000,"text":"Look at what this does. This is a simple piece of behavioral economics."},{"time":641000,"text":"The best way to get someone to cut their electricity bill"},{"time":644000,"text":"is to show them their own spending,"},{"time":646000,"text":"to show them what their neighbors are spending,"},{"time":649000,"text":"and then show what an energy conscious neighbor is spending."},{"time":652000,"text":"That sort of behavioral economics"},{"time":655000,"text":"can transform people's behavior"},{"time":657000,"text":"in a way that all the bullying and all the information"},{"time":660000,"text":"and all the badgering from a government cannot possibly achieve."},{"time":664000,"text":"Other examples are recycling."},{"time":666000,"text":"We all know we need to recycle more."},{"time":668000,"text":"How do we make it happen?"},{"time":670000,"text":"All the proof from America is that actually, if you pay people to recycle,"},{"time":674000,"text":"if you give them a carrot rather than a stick,"},{"time":676000,"text":"you can transform their behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"So what does all this add up to?"},{"time":681000,"text":"Here are my two favorite U.S. speeches of the last 50 years."},{"time":689000,"text":"Obviously, here we have JFK with that incredibly simple"},{"time":693000,"text":"and powerful formulation,"},{"time":695000,"text":"\"Ask not what your country can do for you; ask what you can do for your country,\""},{"time":700000,"text":"an incredibly noble sentiment."},{"time":702000,"text":"But when he made that speech, what could you do"},{"time":705000,"text":"to build the stronger, better society?"},{"time":707000,"text":"You could fight for your country, you could die for your country,"},{"time":710000,"text":"you could serve in your country's civil service,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but you didn't really have the information and the knowledge"},{"time":716000,"text":"and the ability to help build the stronger society in the way that you do now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721000,"text":"And I think an even more wonderful speech,"},{"time":724000,"text":"which I'm going to read a big chunk of,"},{"time":728000,"text":"which sums up what I said at the beginning"},{"time":730000,"text":"about believing there is more to life than money,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and more that we should try and measure than money."},{"time":736000,"text":"And it is Robert Kennedy's beautiful description"},{"time":738000,"text":"of why gross national product captures so little:"},{"time":741000,"text":"It \"does not allow for the health of our children,"},{"time":744000,"text":"the quality of their education, or the joy of their play."},{"time":747000,"text":"It does not include the beauty of our poetry or the strength of our marriages,"},{"time":751000,"text":"the intelligence of our public debate."},{"time":753000,"text":"It measures neither our wit nor our courage,"},{"time":756000,"text":"neither our wisdom nor our learning,"},{"time":758000,"text":"neither our compassion nor our devotion to our country."},{"time":761000,"text":"It measures everything, in short,"},{"time":763000,"text":"except that which makes life worthwhile.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"Again, a sentiment that was so noble and beautifully put 40 years ago,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and a beautiful dream 40 years ago,"},{"time":774000,"text":"but now with the huge advances in information technology,"},{"time":778000,"text":"with the massive changes in behavioral economics,"},{"time":781000,"text":"with all that we know about how you advance well-being,"},{"time":785000,"text":"that if we combine those insights"},{"time":787000,"text":"of giving power to people, and using information to make that possible,"},{"time":791000,"text":"and using the insight of going with the grain of human nature,"},{"time":795000,"text":"while at the same time, understanding why people behave in the way they do,"},{"time":799000,"text":"it is a dream more easy to realize today"},{"time":803000,"text":"than it was when it was made in that beautiful speech 40 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":809000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}